CuInSexS2−x CQDs are a heavy-metal-free alternative to CdSe and PbSe(S) CQDs43–46. Due to their narrow bandgap (composition tunable between 1 and 1.5 eV in the bulk form), they are excellent sunlight harvesters that have been extensively explored in the context of applications in PVs33,44 and luminescent solar concentrators47. Several recent works have also investigated charge-transport properties of CuInSexS2−x CQDs from the standpoint of prospective applications in electronic devices48–50. These studies have revealed a considerable effect of internal native defects on electrical conductance not observable in PbSe(S) and CdSe CQDs. In particular, as-prepared CuInSexS2−x CQDs display p-type transport characteristics before surface treatments, which has been ascribed to a large abundance of acceptors in the form of metal vacancies (VCu′\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
